{"id":"a018","internalId":"312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f","createdAt":"2026-01-28T06:53:20.260Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-24T11:10:18.771Z","status":{"code":"PUBLISHED","name":"Published"},"assessmentType":{"code":"CAR_ASSISTED_DRIVING","name":"Car Assisted Driving"},"assessmentDiagrams":[],"publicationDate":"2024-10-23","publicationYear":"2024","ratingYear":2024,"SPRefNumber":"a018","umbracoRefNumber":null,"rescueSheetURL":null,"greenNcapURL":null,"frontalImageURL":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__5ea148ddb5c71d9d_original.png","frontalImage":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__5ea148ddb5c71d9d_original.png","altText":null,"width":504,"height":335,"formats":{"large":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__576852a6b675daf1_lg.webp","width":504,"height":335},"small":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__e68fa9612eb41f8c_sm.webp","width":320,"height":213},"medium":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__576852a6b675daf1_md.webp","width":504,"height":335},"xlarge":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__576852a6b675daf1_xl.webp","width":504,"height":335},"thumbnail":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/312a2304-8c08-4327-bc1d-9107714cc12f/byd-atto3-2025-bosch-2025-a033__13ab35cab60b8b41_thumb.webp","width":156,"height":104}}},"newsMarketURL":"https://news.euroncap.com/safercars/choose-a-car/byd-atto-3---euro-ncap-2024-assisted-driving-results---not-recommended-grading/s/97723ea6-7b1b-4798-b231-9e667d0d67f4","resultApplicability":"all","comments":"<p>BYD’s appropriately named Adaptive Cruise Control’ accurately portrays system functionality. The promotional material and the handbook correctly indicate the limitations of the system capabilities. System status information is displayed but there is no headup display. Sensing that the driver’s hands remain on the steering wheel was not robust, and the car lost points in this area, and for driver monitoring more generally. However, the system balances driver steering input with lane guidance, promoting co-operative driving.</p><p>The ATTO 3 uses camera inputs to detect speed limit signs. However, the speed limiter reacted to some temporary and/or conditional speed limits as though they were primary limits, and did not meet Euro NCAP’s requirements. There is no speed adaptation for upcoming road features such as curves and junctions. The ATTO 3 responds to avoid a collision in some of the ACC test scenarios. The driver is supported through the S-Bend, but the car is kept fully in lane only at the lowest test speed. A lane-change assist function is not provided. In case of an unresponsive driver, the ATTO 3 disengages the lane centering function but keeps the adaptive cruise control active. If the radar or camera is blocked the car provides a warning but does not disengage.</p><p>The BYD ATTO 3 provides modest levels of driver engagement and vehicle assistance. However, it is in the area of safety backup and, specifically, the lack of action which is taken in case of an unresponsive driver, that the car performs poorly. Overall, the system is Not Recommended for highway assistance.</p>","testedHandOfDrive":null,"assessmentTags":[],"assessmentData":{"carAssistedDriving":{"disclaimer":"When using Assisted Driving Systems (also known as SAE Level 2 systems), a driver’s responsibilities include monitoring the system’s control of speed, braking and steering at all times, strict compliance with traffic rules, and maintaining situational awareness throughout the journey. Certain situations might negatively influence the system’s performance (e.g. poor weather, faded lane markings, construction zones, exiting a tunnel), resulting in a sudden interruption of the lateral and/or longitudinal support (system disengagement). Moreover, the system may fail to detect certain road users such as motorcyclists not directly in front of the vehicle, or stationary objects. Appropriate fitness to drive is critical for safe travel, even when using Assisted Driving Systems. Visual distraction (e.g. eyes off the road), impairment (e.g. drowsiness, intoxication) as well as unresponsiveness, poses high risks. It is highly recommended to keep your hands on the steering wheel at all times to ensure immediate reaction when the system disengages.","domain":{"highway":"RECOMMENDED","interUrban":"RECOMMENDED","urban":"NOT_RECOMMENDED"},"nicePublicationDate":"October 2024","assistedDrivingPerformance":{"assistanceCompetence":{"score":55,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":55,"driverEngagement":{"score":64.9,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":64.9,"elements":{"consumerInformation":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN","elements":{"marketingMaterial":{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UxbA6sjaUho","viewDate":"15/10/2024"},"quickStartGuide":true,"handbook":{"url":"https://euroncap.blob.core.windows.net/media/83330/byd-atto-3-2024-a018_vehicle-handbook_driving-assistance-functions.pdf"}}},"systemStatus":{"score":14.9,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"YELLOW","elements":{"continuousSystemStatusIndicator":"GREEN","systemStatusChangeIndicator":"ORANGE"}},"driverMonitoring":{"score":0,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"RED","elements":{"handsOnMonitoring":"RED","directDriverMonitoring":"RED"}},"drivingCollaboration":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN","elements":{"increaseSteeringTorque":"GREEN","overrideResponse":"GREEN","comment":"System continues to assist while driver steers to avoid obstacle"}}}},"vehicleAssistance":{"score":55.